{
  "stem": "14060.6",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "It's unbelievable what people did because it was considered the semi-death sentence if you were taken into the Munka Tabor and in turn sent to Ukraine.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So there were two stages.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Once you were in Munka Tabor, you didn't know where they were sending you.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Some stayed in Hungary.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Not all of them were sent out.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It went through [INAUDIBLE], or whichever method they used because they used them for building railways and various jobs in the country as well, which was not as lethal as the Ukraine or the Russian front, but certainly no pleasure.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And my brother, having just completed his matric and his picture being in a most elegant shop window with all his friends being a perfectly normal person, has, has tried to, to, to, to learn to imitate a mental illness, i.e.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Depression.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because depression is very difficult to, to detect, as you know, medicine-- people can tell you.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And this is an up and down feeling.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I remember that he had to go to Gyor-- which was quite a distance-- to a mental institute that he was a inmate of there.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And it was also a dangerous exercise because the military doctors who were not-- were the worst anti-Semites, who practically made half-dead people being fit to be taken in.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They, they-- as the years went on, in '42, '43, it became politically impossible to get out of.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Used the method that where they suspected that somebody was faking a mental illness, they sent them up to Budapest to one of the institutes, and they gave them electric shock treatments.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Now, that's not funny when you are well.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It's not funny when you're not well as well, but at least it does have a certain sort of improving effect, but he didn't.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
